To compress a directory on Linux or Unix
	$ tar czvf <archive_name>.tar.gz <directory_name> --exclude=<directory_to_exclude>
	-c create archive
	-z compress using gzip
	-v verbose -- display progress
	-f archive file name

To compress a directory on Linux or Unix
	$ tar xzvf <archive_name>.tar.gz 

To extract:
	$ tar -xf <name>.tar.gz


Zip

Zip a file:
	$ zip file.zip file

Zip a dir:
	$ zip directory.zip directory -r

